* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˌæ.kəˈpɛl.ə/|/ˌæ.kæˈpɛl.ə/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˌɑ kə.ˈpɛl.ə/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɛlə|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-us-a_cappella.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|head=[[a]] [[cappella]]|-}}

# {{context|music|lang=en}} In a manner of a [[choir]] with no [[instrumental]] [[accompaniment]]; literally "in the style of the (Sistine) Chapel (in Rome)"; such as a musical Mass done ''a cappella''.{{defdate|First attested in the late 19th century.}}<ref name=SOED>Brown, Lesley, ed. ''The Shorter Oxford English Dictionary.'' 5th. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2003.</ref>
#: ''Groups of teens singing ''a cappella'' on street corners got recording contracts.''
# {{context|obsolete|music|lang=en}} In ''[[alla breve]]'' time.

